<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Conservation status in Cameroon.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Cusset, Fl. Cameroon 30: 56" authorityYear="1987" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Zehnderia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Zehnderia microgyna" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microgyna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Zehnderia microgyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is listed on http://www.iucnredlist.org. as Critically Endangered (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2010-3.RLTS.T185538A8431595.en" author="Ghogue, J-P" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B47" refString="Ghogue, J-P, 2010s. Zehnderiamicrogyna. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e.T185538A8431595. https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2010-3.RLTS.T185538A8431595.en" title="Zehnderiamicrogyna. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e. T 185538 A 8431595." url="https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2010-3.RLTS.T185538A8431595.en" year="2010 s">Ghogue 2010s</bibRefCitation>
). The taxon is known from only one locality. The extent of occurrence of 
<taxonomicName genus="Z." lsidName="Z. microgyna" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="microgyna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Z. microgyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the area of occupancy are estimated at about 4 km2 each. There is a dam built on the Sanaga River, the habitat of the species. Based on that threat, and the fact that the species is known only from one locality and the continuous decline of vegetation cover in the area, and extent and/or quality of habitat, 
<taxonomicName genus="Z." lsidName="Z. microgyna" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="microgyna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Z. microgyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here assessed as Critically Endangered. IUCN Red List Category: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Critically Endangered CRB1+2ab (ii, iii).</emphasis>
</paragraph>
